:: Dido {"position":"100,1700","size":"100,100"}
On the pyre, Dido is burning where she has burnt for 2,000 years.

The scent of her sour embers says something about the lily of the valley.

'Stay,' she says, 'My Carthage is meant for you. Lily is in her valley and will not return. Rest here and think no more about your England.'

(link: "⟡ LORE: Her Dying Words ⟡")[<div class="lore-box">
Littora littoribus contraria, fluctibus undas<br>
Impresor: arma armis: pugnent ipsig nepotes:<br>
Liue false Æneas, truest Dido dyes,<br>
Sic sic inuat ire sub umbras.<br>
<br>
Shores against shores; waves, waves;<br>
I curse, arms against arms, you and your children.<br>
Live false Aeneus, truest Dido dies,<br>
So, so happily I go, under the shades.
</div>]

(if: $knowsAboutPage is true and $hasMissingPage is false)[Among the flames, you see something that shouldn't be there — a page, curling at the edges but not yet consumed. The writing on it shifts and writhes.

[[Reach into the flames|Rescue the page]]]

(if: $confidence <= 15)[[[Remain in Carthage|Stay in Carthage]]
(if: $haunts's length >= 3)[[[Try The Green Sea|LINE 2]]](else:)[//Find more haunts then go to The Green Sea//]

[[Return to the shore|The coast of Carthage]]]
(else:)[Not yet. The game's not played to death.

(if: $haunts's length >= 3)[[[Try The Green Sea|LINE 2]]](else:)[//Find more haunts then go to The Green Sea//]

[[Return to the shore|The coast of Carthage]]]


