:: Jeffrey conversation {"position":"700,1100","size":"100,100"}
'Are you alright?' he says. 'You don't look well.'

'I've got a book to sell.'

'That I can see. They're running from you, will have been all night. Have you seen my cow?'

He seems unsure if he's lost it or if he's asking if you'd found it. It's standing behind the bar, lets out a noise.

He drinks.

'Speak to Lackland, he'll be around. You'll find your own way out.'

