      </svg>

      <!-- Lattice pub window at top -->
      <svg class="pillars-lattice" viewBox="0 0 300 36" width="100%" height="36" preserveAspectRatio="none">
        <defs>
          <linearGradient id="latEdge" x1="0" x2="1">
            <stop offset="0%"   stop-color="#7ab8cc" stop-opacity="0"/>
            <stop offset="15%"  stop-color="#7ab8cc" stop-opacity="0.55"/>
            <stop offset="85%"  stop-color="#7ab8cc" stop-opacity="0.55"/>
            <stop offset="100%" stop-color="#7ab8cc" stop-opacity="0"/>
          </linearGradient>
          <pattern id="dLat" x="0" y="0" width="14" height="24" patternUnits="userSpaceOnUse">
            <path d="M7,0 L14,12 L7,24 L0,12 Z" fill="none" stroke="#7ab8cc" stroke-width="0.7" opacity="0.48"/>
          </pattern>
          <mask id="latMask">
            <rect x="0" y="0" width="300" height="36" fill="url(#latEdge)"/>
          </mask>
        </defs>
        <rect x="0" y="0" width="300" height="36" fill="url(#dLat)" mask="url(#latMask)"/>
        <line x1="0" y1="34" x2="300" y2="34" stroke="url(#latEdge)" stroke-width="1.2"/>
      </svg>

(set: $confidence to $confidence - 5)

He nods, pulls the manuscript towards him. He lights another cigarette.

The bar, which had been very loud, seems quieter now, while he reads the title page then turns immediately to somewhere in the middle.

He reads a little there, then turns again to another page and reads that too. He does this several times, while the bar is getting louder in your ears, until it seems about to drop.

'Not for me', he says. 'Have you tried America?'

You thank him, say goodbye, and make to leave but he calls you back:

'And by the way, tell Copper I said hello.'

(set: $knowsCopperWord to true)

He pauses, as if remembering something.

'Oh — and if you're ever in Cecil Court, look up the antiquarian. Queer fellow, but he knows things. Things about books that shouldn't exist.'

(set: $knowsCecilCourt to true)

[[Try again|Dean Street]]
<span class="guided-link">[[Head for the night bus|Meet Jeffrey Bernard]]</span>

    </div>

:: The novelist {"position":"700,550","size":"100,100"}
<svg class="french-rule" viewBox="0 0 300 44" width="100%" height="44" preserveAspectRatio="none"><defs><linearGradient id="frAmb" x1="0" x2="1"><stop offset="0%" stop-color="#a06010" stop-opacity="0"/><stop offset="10%" stop-color="#b07020" stop-opacity="0.6"/><stop offset="50%" stop-color="#c88020" stop-opacity="0.72"/><stop offset="90%" stop-color="#b07020" stop-opacity="0.6"/><stop offset="100%" stop-color="#a06010" stop-opacity="0"/></linearGradient><linearGradient id="frLn" x1="0" x2="1"><stop offset="0%" stop-color="#c8a86a" stop-opacity="0"/><stop offset="10%" stop-color="#c8a86a" stop-opacity="0.95"/><stop offset="90%" stop-color="#c8a86a" stop-opacity="0.95"/><stop offset="100%" stop-color="#c8a86a" stop-opacity="0"/></linearGradient></defs><rect x="0" y="16" width="300" height="22" fill="url(#frAmb)"/><line x1="0" y1="16" x2="300" y2="16" stroke="url(#frLn)" stroke-width="2"/><line x1="0" y1="38" x2="300" y2="38" stroke="url(#frLn)" stroke-width="2"/><rect x="61" y="21" width="8" height="16" rx="1" fill="#002395"/><rect x="63" y="17" width="4" height="6" rx="1" fill="#002395"/><rect x="79" y="19" width="9" height="18" rx="1" fill="#f0f0f0"/><rect x="81" y="16" width="5" height="5" rx="1" fill="#f0f0f0"/><rect x="97" y="20" width="7" height="17" rx="1" fill="#ed2939"/><rect x="99" y="17" width="3" height="5" rx="1" fill="#ed2939"/><rect x="197" y="21" width="8" height="16" rx="1" fill="#002395"/><rect x="199" y="17" width="4" height="6" rx="1" fill="#002395"/><rect x="215" y="19" width="9" height="18" rx="1" fill="#f0f0f0"/><rect x="217" y="16" width="5" height="5" rx="1" fill="#f0f0f0"/><rect x="233" y="20" width="7" height="17" rx="1" fill="#ed2939"/><rect x="235" y="17" width="3" height="5" rx="1" fill="#ed2939"/><polygon points="150,20 155,27 150,34 145,27" fill="#c8a86a" opacity="0.8"/><polygon points="150,22 153,27 150,32 147,27" fill="#a06010" opacity="0.85"/></svg>

(set: $confidence to $confidence - 8)

He's been reading it for longer than is comfortable for either of you.

At last, he pushes it back and asks: 'Is this yours?'

Before you can answer, he says, 'I don't know.'

(if: not ($haunts contains $haunt2))[(if: $hauntExplained is false)[(set: $hauntExplained to true)
<div class="lore-box">
<strong>⟡ HAUNTS ⟡</strong>

Tonight, Soho will mark you. Here, in our mutual dream, we call these marks 'haunts'. You'll gather them as you wander the night and its stages. Seek them: you'll need them to get out.
</div>]
(set: $haunts to $haunts + (a: $haunt2))
(set: $exploredSinceFrench to false)

<div class="haunt-box">
<div class="haunt-header">⟡ HAUNT COLLECTED ⟡</div>
<div class="haunt-name">THE REFUSAL</div>
<div class="haunt-description">Chin up, lad, there's always poetry.</div>
</div>]

[[Back to Dean Street|Dean Street]]

<svg class="french-rule" viewBox="0 0 300 24" width="100%" height="24" preserveAspectRatio="none"><defs><linearGradient id="frC" x1="0" x2="1"><stop offset="0%" stop-color="#c8a86a" stop-opacity="0"/><stop offset="45%" stop-color="#c8a86a" stop-opacity="0.55"/><stop offset="100%" stop-color="#c8a86a" stop-opacity="0"/></linearGradient><linearGradient id="frD" x1="0" x2="1"><stop offset="0%" stop-color="#c8a86a" stop-opacity="0"/><stop offset="45%" stop-color="#c8a86a" stop-opacity="0.28"/><stop offset="100%" stop-color="#c8a86a" stop-opacity="0"/></linearGradient></defs><line x1="0" y1="7" x2="300" y2="7" stroke="url(#frD)" stroke-width="0.5"/><line x1="0" y1="12" x2="300" y2="12" stroke="url(#frC)" stroke-width="1.2"/><svg x="140" y="0" width="20" height="24" viewBox="-12 -2 24 26" preserveAspectRatio="xMidYMid meet"><g fill="#c8a86a" opacity="0.75"><path d="M0,15 C-3,10 -4,2 0,-1 C4,2 3,10 0,15Z"/><path d="M-1,13 C-4,10 -8,5 -9,3 C-9,5 -8,6 -6,5 C-3,8 -1,11 0,13Z"/><path d="M1,13 C4,10 8,5 9,3 C9,5 8,6 6,5 C3,8 1,11 0,13Z"/><rect x="-8" y="14" width="16" height="2.5" rx="0.5"/><ellipse cx="0" cy="20" rx="2.5" ry="2"/></g></svg></svg>

:: The phone call {"position":"100,1100","size":"100,100"}
(set: $hadPhoneCall to true)
(set: $confidence to $confidence - 5)

The phone rings behind the bar.

It's Aoife.

'The heating's gone. Will you be home soon? She won't leave-off crying.'

'Later tonight.'

'Much later?'

'Yes. Goodnight. I love you.'

Through the fumes, vapours and drink, you recognise a man.

[[Talk to the halfcut literary critic|Talk to the critic]]


:: Things turn up {"position":"1100,300","size":"100,100"}
'Things turn up', said the poet.

'Here is your throat back, thanks for the loan.'

[[Try me again|Dean Street]]


