:: Turn to Copper {"position":"1600,850","size":"100,100"}
<!-- Swinging bulb -->
    <div class="cellar-bulb-wrap">
      <svg width="48" height="90" viewBox="0 0 48 90">
        <!-- Wire from ceiling -->
        <line x1="24" y1="0" x2="24" y2="30" stroke="#888878" stroke-width="1.4" opacity="0.75"/>
        <!-- Socket cap -->
        <rect x="17" y="28" width="14" height="10" rx="2.5"
              fill="rgba(80,78,65,0.9)" stroke="rgba(160,155,120,0.7)" stroke-width="1"/>
        <!-- Socket ring detail -->
        <rect x="19" y="36" width="10" height="3" rx="1"
              fill="none" stroke="rgba(150,145,110,0.55)" stroke-width="0.8"/>
        <!-- Outer glow halo -->
        <ellipse cx="24" cy="60" rx="20" ry="22"
                 fill="rgba(255,245,160,0.12)"/>
        <!-- Bulb body — pear shape, bright and solid -->
        <path d="M24,38 C16,38 10,45 10,55 C10,67 16,78 24,78 C32,78 38,67 38,55 C38,45 32,38 24,38 Z"
              fill="rgba(255,252,210,0.95)" stroke="rgba(220,210,160,0.6)" stroke-width="0.8"/>
        <!-- Inner warm core -->
        <ellipse cx="24" cy="57" rx="9" ry="11"
                 fill="rgba(255,240,120,0.55)"/>
        <!-- Filament — W-shape -->
        <path d="M18,60 L20,53 L24,58 L28,53 L30,60"
              fill="none" stroke="rgba(255,200,40,0.95)" stroke-width="1.4" stroke-linejoin="round"/>
        <!-- Neck base ring -->
        <rect x="20" y="75" width="8" height="3" rx="1"
              fill="rgba(200,195,155,0.65)" stroke="none"/>
      </svg>
    </div>

    <div class="cellar-scene">
      <div class="cellar-light"></div>
'Salvu Copper' is a name you know and now you're putting a face to it.

Since the Twins went down in '68, his work's been easier. He's run his little fiefdom – pornography, strip clubs, hookers (the sorts of work that old fashioned East End crooks will swear blind they don't touch) – very nicely, though lately he's feeling the heat.

At the far end of the cellar, at a simple wooden table, sits 'Quiet' Frankie Muscat, who seems to you like nothing so much as a planet, the sort of man with moons. Yes, he is big, but his gravity comes, mostly, from his silence and a sense of power unused.

Opposite him (and her presence surprises you) is a poet you know, an American girl who comes from banking money, called Ashton Granger. You agreed long ago to pretend not to notice each other, should you accidentally meet. She twirls her hair and scribbles without looking at the page, and gives Quiet Frankie a kind of angry come-hither look.

Copper speaks:

'What have you got to say for yourself?'

(if: $knowsCopperWord)[[[Tell Copper: "I SAID HELLO."|Copper accepts]]
[[Say nothing|Copper confronts]]]
(else:)[[[Say nothing|Copper confronts]]]
    </div>

:: Watch the decider {"position":"1200,1300","size":"100,100"}
Harsent wins it. Smash to the corner.

'Fresh blood,' says Harsent. 'Fancy a game?'

'House rules,' says Clegg. 'Winner plays the stranger.'

[[Challenge Harsent|Challenge Harsent]]
[[Challenge Clegg|Challenge Clegg]]
[[I'd rather just watch|Watch them play]]


:: Watch them play {"position":"1400,1300","size":"100,100"}
You watch them play.

'Lackland's sitting on something,' says Clegg.

'Lackland's always sitting on something,' says Harsent. 'It's what he does instead of standing for anything.'

(set: $confidence to $confidence + 5)

Harsent tosses you a paddle. 'House rules.'

[[Take the paddle|Challenge Harsent]]


