:: Wrong door {"position":"1600,550","size":"100,100"}
You've ballsed this right up. It's already getting late.

Trisha's is close by and you can always try there. You're not a member these days, so who knows if you'll get in.

[[They know me|Failure: Trisha's]]
<span class="guided-link">[[I might as well give it a try|Success: Trisha's]]</span>


:: You speak to the poet {"position":"1400,450","size":"100,100"}
(set: $metRed to true)
'Red!' you say. He looks up at first, then towards you without looking at you.

'I need to sell a book.'

'Sell yourself,' he says. 'Things turn up.'

You understand.

As you turn, you strike, in the cool and marbling air, a vein of his perfume, which you recognise, because you once loved a woman who wore that scent, as lily-of-the-valley.

(set: $confidence to $confidence - 3)

[[Walk on|LINE 1]]


:: You wait for him to speak {"position":"1400,350","size":"100,100"}
(set: $confidence to $confidence - 3)
You stand near Red for a while, outside the ginger light. He seems to be somewhere else entirely.

Like a tiger in the Taiga, moving strong and low through heavy blizzard, whose footprints fill as soon as they are made, what Red leaves of himself upon the street is trackless at your shutter-speed; he is an accumulaton, mostly, of scents, and the drifting bergs of ash he drops in the puddle at his feet, which, even when they should be dead, are, by some feeling wind, awakened into transitory brightness.

What could you say? What dare you say?

//Perhaps you should say something.//

<span class="guided-link">[[Speak to him|You speak to the poet]]</span>
[[Leave and try again|Dean Street]]


