::Lackland&#39;s Back Room {"position":"1200,1150"}
Downstairs. A table tennis table, green as money.

Two men: John Clegg, bookseller. David Harsent, poet. 20-20. Match point.

[[Watch the decider|Watch the decider]]

[[Slip away quietly|Watch the decider]]

::Martin Lackland&#39;s Office {"position":"1200,1000"}
(set: $exploredSinceFrench to true)
You find the building on Frith Street, on the door: M. Lackland.

You knock and he buzzes you in. You climb two doglegs to his rooms.

He lifts the needle from his record, sinks his glass then tops it up again (more scotch and soda).

(link: "⟡ What's he listening to? ⟡")[<div class="lore-box">
On the turntable was //2 + 2 + 1 = Ponderosa Twins Plus One//, by the Ponderosa Twins Plus One, more specifically the song 'Bound', on which the producer Bobby Massey has writing credit. Massey had been with the O'Jays and would go on, after the turning of the millennium, to be listed as executive producer on a film with the Spice Girls and two films with David Beckham. But he, like the rest of that group, was from Cleveland, Ohio, in the U.S.A.

I'm writing this in February, 2026; if you're reading it you'll have lived at least a touch longer. So we'll know that Ye sample that song in 'Bound 2', when he still went by Kanye West. But Lackland knows nothing about that.

He has a Garrard 401 screwed into the wall, with an SME arm bolted on and a Shure cartridge. This means that he can play his music loudly.

He found the album at Dobell's several lunches ago, and it's hardly been silent since.
</div>]

He turns to his desk with both his elbows and setting them down individually, says, 'You were sent here by Jeffrey?'

You nod.

'Well, give it here.'

You lay the manuscript down.

He reads the first page; then the last; then a page from somewhere in the middle.
(if: $confidence >= 60)[He sets it down as one might set a toddler down on the floor.

'This isn't bad. Have you got a job? A wife? How long can you give to me? You've something but there's work to do; lots of work.'

This is as close as you've come to anything.
(set: $confidence to $confidence + 20)

[[Leave with a smile|Dean Street]]]
(else:)[He sets it down.

'This isn't there.'

You knew that.
(set: $confidence to $confidence - 5)

[[Leave|Dean Street]]]

(if: $knowsCopperSecret is true)[You notice a door at the back of the office you hadn't seen before. Or perhaps you had, but now it means something.

[[Whisper "Valletta"|Lackland's Back Room]]]

::Milk Jeffrey Bernard&#39;s Cow {"position":"900,1300"}
You lie on the Dean Street pavement like a mechanic under a chassis, take an udder in your fist and squeeze it, gingerly.

A little warm milk plashes on your lips. It tastes of grass and moonlight and something you can't name.

'This,' you think, 'is why he is unwell.'

But strangely, you feel better. The milk has settled something in you.

(set: $sobriety to $sobriety + 15)
(set: $confidence to $confidence + 10)
[[Get up and try again|Dean Street]]

::O&#39;Flatterly introduction {"position":"300,1700"}
At that, Inish O'Flatterly looks up. His eyes, magnified by the glass, are the pale blue of photographs left too long in the sun.

'Clegg, is it? The critic?' He waves a hand like a man shooing pigeons. 'Doesn't matter. They all send me the strays eventually.'

He gestures at a stool. You sit. It wobbles; everything here wobbles, held together by dust and habit.

'You're a writer.' Not a question. 'I can smell the desperation. It comes off you like cheap cologne. What are you working on?'

You tell him. He listens with the patience of a man who has heard ten thousand stories and filed them all away in that labyrinthine skull.

'Interesting,' he says, when you've finished. 'Not good, necessarily. But interesting.'

He leans forward. The lamp throws his face into geography: hills of cheekbone, valleys of wrinkle.

'I'll make you a deal. I'm looking for something—a page, torn from a book that shouldn't exist. It's been floating around Soho for decades. Someone has it. They don't know what they have.'

(if: $hasMissingPage is true)[Your hand goes to your pocket. The page. You'd almost forgotten; the night has that effect.

[[Show him the page|Return the page]]]
(else:)[[[What book?|O'Flatterly's quest]]

[[I'll keep an eye out|Dean Street]](if: not ($haunts contains $haunt6))[ <span class="missed-haunt">You missed a haunt</span>]]

::O&#39;Flatterly&#39;s Gift {"position":"500,1950"}
'If I may, let me give you small thanks.'

From beneath the counter he produces a small glass vial. It contains a slice of something resembling jerky.

'This,' he says, 'is a slice of the liver of Percy Bysshe Shelley. It was cut from his body, as it burned on the beach at Viareggio, by Trelawny, who mistook his liver for his heart. Swallow it if you ever get close to the end.'

(set: $returnedPage to true)
(set: $confidence to $confidence + 25)

