</div>]

[[Back to Dean Street|Dean Street]]

::O&#39;Flatterly&#39;s quest {"position":"300,1850"}
O'Flatterly's eyes catch the light; for a moment he looks like something older than he is, older than the century.

'A manuscript. Sixteenth century. A play that was never performed—could never be performed. The author wrote it in a language that hadn't been invented yet.'

He produces a leather-bound volume from beneath a sediment of papers. It falls open to a wound: the ragged edge where a page has been torn.

'Forty years I've been tracking the pieces. This is the last. Page 47. Someone in Soho has it—I'm certain as death. In a pub, perhaps. Used as a bookmark. Tucked into a wallet. Folded into a pocket and forgotten.'

He fixes you with those milk-bottle eyes.

'Find it for me, and I'll give you something in return. Something that might help with your... situation.'

(set: $knowsAboutPage to true)

<div class="lore-box">
<strong>⟡ QUEST ⟡</strong>

Inish O'Flatterly is searching for a missing page — Page 47 of an impossible manuscript. It's somewhere in Soho. Find it and return it to him.
</div>

[[I'll look for it|Dean Street]](if: not ($haunts contains $haunt6))[ <span class="missed-haunt">You missed a haunt</span>]

::O&#39;Flatterly&#39;s shop {"position":"300,1620"}
The sign reads: I. O'FLATTERLY, dealer in books.

You waltz in.

Strenuously reading, Inish O'Flatterly sits at the thick wooden counter. He does not look to notice you, yet neither does his shop lack any welcome.

[[I was sent by Clegg|O'Flatterly introduction]]

